---
description: Boolean properties read as yes/no questions; implementation answers one
globs: "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: true
---

# Properties as Questions

Name **boolean** properties so they read as **questions**. The implementation
answers that question, and only that question.

`isprotected` — "is this protected?" `ismethod` — "is this a method?"
`isinit` — "is this the class constructor?" Each property is one predicate.
The reader asks the object a question; the object answers. No compound
questions (avoid "is_valid_and_ready" — split into two properties or a
single clear predicate).

For non-boolean properties, the name should still be a noun or noun phrase
that describes what is returned: `signature`, `docstring`, `children`.
The property returns that thing and nothing more.
